\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 However, squirrels are very careful while gathering t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
heir food. They don't store fruits and meat, the kind of food that decays quickly. If they gathered them, they would become hungry in the wintertime. For this reason, squirrels collect only durable dry fruits like walnuts, hazelnuts and cones. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 It is Allah\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 Who gives this knowledge to squirrels at birth and enables them to take their nutrition. Here, we witness one of the attributes of Allah: Allah is "ar-Razzaq", that is, "the One Who continually provides sustenance to every living being He has created".

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Sq\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 uirrels store their food for winter by burying it in various places. Thanks to their perfect sense of smell, they can detect the smell of nuts covered by 30 centimetres (12 inches)of snow. 
