ses to mark their territory. This substance, secreted from the glands under their eyes, informs other gazelles that this field is already occupied. Reindeer, on the other hand, have scent glands on the tip of their hind feet with which they mark their ter
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 r\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 itory. Rabbits mark their territories with glands on their chins.
