\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 You may ask, "Is it possible that an animal could have a pocket?" Surprisingly, kangaroos have a "pouch" on their bellies where baby kangaroos are fed and protected during their development. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The appearance of a joey (baby kangaroo) whose head appears from\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 its mother's pouch arouses feelings of compassion in us. This baby, coming out of the womb when it was only one centimetre (0.393 inches) long \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  that is before it was fully \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  developed \hich\f0 \endash 
\loch\f0  reached its mother's pouch after a three minute journey.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 There are f\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
our different nipples in the pouch of the mother. The new-born sucks the nipple that issues a milk with just the right temperature and amount of fat for a new-born. The other three nipples, on the other hand, contain milk meeting the needs of an older bab
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 y\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
. In a few weeks, the new-born stops suckling its nipple and finds another nipple from which issues a milk prepared for its own needs. As it grows older, it finds a third nipple with the type of milk specially prepared for its needs. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Children! At this poi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
nt, you must ask yourself the questions, "How can a baby kangaroo one centimetre long know the right nipple that would meets its needs?", "How has the mother kangaroo placed milk in her four nipples with such different ingredients?" What is more, the milk
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
the new-born baby sucks is hotter than the other milk from the other nipples. Their ingredients are also different. This being the case, how did the mother kangaroo manage to heat this milk? How has she added the necessary ingredients to this milk?
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Remembe\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
r, it is not the mother who has accomplished all these things. The mother kangaroo does not even know that the milk issuing from the nipples is different. It is unlikely that she could compute the temperature of the milk produced by her nipples. She canno
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 manage to provide each nipple with different kinds of milk. She cannot even know that they are different. She is only a kangaroo living under Allah's watchful care. Her baby's needs are taken care of by Allah. Our Lord, the All-Compassionate and Most Mer
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 c\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 iful, has placed the most appropriate milk in the most appropriate place for the babies, that is, in the mother's pouch. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 A baby kangaroo spends its first six and a half months in this pouch. After spending the next eight months both in the pouch and outsi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 de, it leaves it once and for all. 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Meanwhile, before the first joey leaves the pouch, a new brother or sister crawls into the pouch. They both live in the same pouch for a long time, without giving any harm to one another. Each joey sucks on the nipple wi
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 th the milk containing just the right ingredients for their needs. Then, how do the two siblings know which nipple to suck? The answer is obvious: by Allah's inspiration.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Kangaroos are awesome with their huge bodies; the body is one and a half metres long \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
and the tail one metre (39 inches) long. Thanks to their long hind limbs, the kangaroo family can traverse a distance of eight metres in only a moment. While running, they maintain balance by their big strong tails. Do you think their feet have become lar
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 g\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
e by coincidence? Or, do you think their mother estimated that they would need large hind limbs to leap? Of course, none of these give us the right answer. Nothing has come into existence accidentally. Allah, the One Who creates everything according to th
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  needs of creatures, has also created kangaroos like all other creatures in their most perfect form.
