\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 One of the most striking characteristics of storks i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
s the way they fly. While flying, they extend their heads forward and push their legs backward. This aesthetic style of storks enables them to fly much faster by cleaving the air aerodynamically. Every year, storks migrate to warm regions because they are
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
vulnerable to cold. That is why when we see storks arriving, we also receive the glad tidings of hot summer days. In the summer season, storks live in the temperate regions that extend from Europe to North Africa and from Turkey to Japan. Before the weath
